This article discusses the 70th anniversary of the Alliance between the United States and the Republic of Korea, which was formed during the Korean War. The article highlights the bravery and sacrifice of American and Korean service members who fought side-by-side during the war. It mentions the visit of President Yoon to the Korean War Veterans Memorial, where wreaths were laid in honor of the fallen soldiers. The article emphasizes that the alliance between the two countries is based on shared beliefs in democracy, security, and freedom. It also recognizes the thousands of US troops who went missing in action during the war, including Army Corporal Luther H. Story, whose remains were recently identified and returned to his family. The article concludes by calling for a renewal of commitment to the democratic values for which the Korean War veterans served and sacrificed, and for the observance of National Korean War Veterans Armistice Day on July 27, 2023.